task.summary: Fixed Batch File that Builds React Code
-Added Data for Timer in assessment -Added Data for Hint in question -Added the ability to change a assessment. PATCH /rest/assessment/{ID}

-Added a Usable Assessment Creation for Development.
-Look at Assessments.jsx( All code is in there, Assessment ID is grabed from this.getAssessmentID() )

-Big Commit!!!! - Finished the Functionality of Assessment(Which Includes the Flow that was specified) - Finished design for main assessments page, aswell as some of the child pages - Added Structure inside of Assessments.jsx to handle everybodies part.(Please Search You Name inside of Assessments.jsx)
- Added Better Comments and Some More Instructions to finish this iteration smoothly
-Mat Please Look at API file... There are some mis understandings on How EventHandler works

A Coupe of things. - Fixed some CSS issues that caused bootstrap to mess up current design - Added Tests for EventHandler(Detailed) - Created Classes to help testing for Assessments page. - Significant improvment in test coverage for the Assessments page - Fixed some of the code due to issues in tests.

After seeing our evaluation today we realized that the missing "Chrome" caused the confusion on our actual testing. This change is to be used for the next iteration and not the current iteration seeing that it has already finished.
Venkat - This commit is meant to make sure this doesnt happen again for the next iteration.
